==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pilgrimage
<hw>Pil"grim*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>pilgrimage</ets>, <ets>pelgrinage</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>p⟦egrave⟧lerinage</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The journey of a
pilgrim; a long journey; especially, a journey to a shrine or other
sacred place. Fig., the journey of human life.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The days of the years of my <qex>pilgrimage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xlvii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tedious and wearisome time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In prison hast thou spent a <qex>pilgrimage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Journey; tour; excursion. See
<er>Journey</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilgrimize</ent>⟦br⟧
